hwPoeMIB.name: hwPoeMIB

revisions.description: V1.04, Change the maximum power to 200000

hwPoeMIB.description: The HUAWEI-POE-MIB contains objects to manage POE.

hwPoePower.name: hwPoePower
hwPoePower.description: This object identifies the maximum POE power of the system.

hwPoePowerRsvPercent.name: hwPoePowerRsvPercent
hwPoePowerRsvPercent.description: This object identifies the reserved percent of total POE power.

hwPoePowerUtilizationThreshold.name: hwPoePowerUtilizationThreshold
hwPoePowerUtilizationThreshold.description: This object identifies the utilization threshold of total POE power.

hwPoeSlotTable.name: hwPoeSlotTable
hwPoeSlotTable.description: This object indicates the slot configuration table of POE.

hwPoeSlotEntry.name: hwPoeSlotEntry
hwPoeSlotEntry.description: This object indicates the entry of the slot configuration table of POE.

hwPoeSlotId.name: hwPoeSlotId
hwPoeSlotId.description: This object identifies the slot ID.

hwPoeSlotMaximumPower.name: hwPoeSlotMaximumPower
hwPoeSlotMaximumPower.description: This object identifies the maximum power set by users. The value is expressed in mW.

hwPoeSlotAvailablePower.name: hwPoeSlotAvailablePower
hwPoeSlotAvailablePower.description: This object idenfies the available Power. The value is expressed in mW.

hwPoeSlotReferencePower.name: hwPoeSlotReferencePower
hwPoeSlotReferencePower.description: This object identifies the total reference power of a slot. The value is expressed in mW.

hwPoeSlotConsumingPower.name: hwPoeSlotConsumingPower
hwPoeSlotConsumingPower.description: This object identifies the total consuming power of a slot. The value is expressed in mW.

hwPoeSlotPeakPower.name: hwPoeSlotPeakPower
hwPoeSlotPeakPower.description: This object identifies the total peak power of a slot. The value is expressed in mW.

hwPoeSlotLegacyDetect.name: hwPoeSlotLegacyDetect
hwPoeSlotLegacyDetect.description: This object indicates the compatibility detection of a non-standard device. (1:enable; 2:disable(default))

hwPoeSlotPowerManagementManner.name: hwPoeSlotPowerManagementManner
hwPoeSlotPowerManagementManner.description: This object identifies the power management manner. (1:manual, 2:auto(default)).

hwPoeSlotIsPoeDevice.name: hwPoeSlotIsPoeDevice
hwPoeSlotIsPoeDevice.description: This object indicates whether the device supports PoE.

hwPoeDimmId.name: hwPoeDimmId
hwPoeDimmId.description: This object identifies the DIMM ID.

hwPoeSlotPowerRsvPercent.name: hwPoeSlotPowerRsvPercent
hwPoeSlotPowerRsvPercent.description: This object identifies the reserved percent of POE power in slot.

hwPoeSlotPowerUtilizationThreshold.name: hwPoeSlotPowerUtilizationThreshold
hwPoeSlotPowerUtilizationThreshold.description: This object identifies the utilization threshold of total POE power in slot.

hwPoePortTable.name: hwPoePortTable
hwPoePortTable.description: This object indicates the table that contains the configuration parameters of a POE interface. One entry corresponds to a POE interface.

hwPoePortEntry.name: hwPoePortEntry
hwPoePortEntry.description: This object indicates the entry of POE Port Table.

hwPoePortIfIndex.name: hwPoePortIfIndex
hwPoePortIfIndex.description: This object indicates the interface index.

hwPoePortName.name: hwPoePortName
hwPoePortName.description: This object indicates the interface name.

hwPoePortEnable.name: hwPoePortEnable
hwPoePortEnable.description: This object indicates the enabling status of an interface. (1:enable(default); 2:disable)

hwPoePortPriority.name: hwPoePortPriority
hwPoePortPriority.description: This object identifies the priority of an interface. (1:critical, 2:high, 3:low(default))

hwPoePortMaximumPower.name: hwPoePortMaximumPower
hwPoePortMaximumPower.description: This object identifies the maximum power of an interface.The value is expressed in mW.

hwPoePortPowerOnStatus.name: hwPoePortPowerOnStatus
hwPoePortPowerOnStatus.description: This object indicates the powering status of an interface.

hwPoePortPowerStatus.name: hwPoePortPowerStatus
hwPoePortPowerStatus.description: This object indicates the status of an interface.

hwPoePortPdClass.name: hwPoePortPdClass
hwPoePortPdClass.description: This object identifies the class of a PD.

hwPoePortReferencePower.name: hwPoePortReferencePower
hwPoePortReferencePower.description: This object identifies the guaranteed power of an interface. The value is expressed in mW.

hwPoePortConsumingPower.name: hwPoePortConsumingPower
hwPoePortConsumingPower.description: This object identifies the consuming power of an interface. The value is expressed in mW.

hwPoePortPeakPower.name: hwPoePortPeakPower
hwPoePortPeakPower.description: This object identifies the peak power of an interface. The value is expressed in mW.

hwPoePortAveragePower.name: hwPoePortAveragePower
hwPoePortAveragePower.description: This object identifies the average power of an interface. The value is expressed in mW.

hwPoePortCurrent.name: hwPoePortCurrent
hwPoePortCurrent.description: This object indicates the current of an interface. The value is expressed in mA.

hwPoePortVoltage.name: hwPoePortVoltage
hwPoePortVoltage.description: This object indicates the voltage of an interface. The value is expressed in V.

hwPoePortManualOperation.name: hwPoePortManualOperation
hwPoePortManualOperation.description: This object indicates that a PD connected to an interface is powered on or powered off manually.

hwPoePortPoweroffTimeRangeSwitch.name: hwPoePortPoweroffTimeRangeSwitch
hwPoePortPoweroffTimeRangeSwitch.description: This object indicates whether the time range of POE power off is confugred on the port.

hwPoePortPoweroffTimeRangeName.name: hwPoePortPoweroffTimeRangeName
hwPoePortPoweroffTimeRangeName.description: This object indicates that time range name of POE power off configured on the port.

hwPoePortJudgeTable.name: hwPoePortJudgeTable
hwPoePortJudgeTable.description: This object indicates the table that contains the judgement of whether port supports POE.

hwPoePortJudgeEntry.name: hwPoePortJudgeEntry
hwPoePortJudgeEntry.description: This object indicates the entry of table.

hwPoePortJudgeIfIndex.name: hwPoePortJudgeIfIndex
hwPoePortJudgeIfIndex.description: This object indicates the interface index.

hwPoePortJudgeIsSupport.name: hwPoePortJudgeIsSupport
hwPoePortJudgeIsSupport.description: This object indicates whether the interface supports POE.

hwPoePowerInfoTable.name: hwPoePowerInfoTable
hwPoePowerInfoTable.description: This object indicates the table that contains the power information of POE.

hwPoePowerInfoEntry.name: hwPoePowerInfoEntry
hwPoePowerInfoEntry.description: This object indicates the entry of table.

hwPoePowerInfoDeviceIndex.name: hwPoePowerInfoDeviceIndex
hwPoePowerInfoDeviceIndex.description: This object indicates the device index. Index: reserved/chassis/slot. The index is format by 4 bytes(8bits for 1 byte): reserved is 1 byte(0x00), chassis is 12bits and slot is also 12bits. e.g. chassis=1, slot=0, the index is 0x00001000. If device is chassis, the slot is always 0. If device is box, the chassis is always 0.

hwPoePowerInfoDeviceName.name: hwPoePowerInfoDeviceName
hwPoePowerInfoDeviceName.description: This object indicates the table that contains the name of device.

hwPoePowerInfoDeviceTotalPower.name: hwPoePowerInfoDeviceTotalPower
hwPoePowerInfoDeviceTotalPower.description: This object indicates the table that contains the total power of POE.

hwPoePowerInfoDeviceTotalAvailablePower.name: hwPoePowerInfoDeviceTotalAvailablePower
hwPoePowerInfoDeviceTotalAvailablePower.description: This object indicates the table that contains the total available power of POE.

hwPoePowerInfoDeviceReservedPower.name: hwPoePowerInfoDeviceReservedPower
hwPoePowerInfoDeviceReservedPower.description: This object indicates the table that contains the reserved power of POE.

hwPoePowerInfoDeviceUsedPower.name: hwPoePowerInfoDeviceUsedPower
hwPoePowerInfoDeviceUsedPower.description: This object indicates the table that contains the used power of POE.

hwPoePowerInfoDeviceRemainPower.name: hwPoePowerInfoDeviceRemainPower
hwPoePowerInfoDeviceRemainPower.description: This object indicates the table that contains the remain power of POE.

hwPoePdPriority.name: hwPoePdPriority
hwPoePdPriority.description: This object identifies the PD priority.(1:critical, 2:high, 3:low(default))

hwPoeSlotNum.name: hwPoeSlotNum
hwPoeSlotNum.description: This object identifies the slot ID.

hwPoeCurConsumPower.name: hwPoeCurConsumPower
hwPoeCurConsumPower.description: This object identifies the current consuming power.

hwPoeConsumPowerThreshold.name: hwPoeConsumPowerThreshold
hwPoeConsumPowerThreshold.description: This object identifies the threshold of consuming power.

hwPoeDeviceID.name: hwPoeDeviceID
hwPoeDeviceID.description: This object identifies the device ID.

hwFrameID.name: hwFrameID
hwFrameID.description: This object identifies the CSS Frame ID.

hwPoeChipID.name: hwPoeChipID
hwPoeChipID.description: This object identifies the control chip ID.

hwPoeDimmError.name: hwPoeDimmError
hwPoeDimmError.description: This object indicates the Dimm chip error.

hwPoePowerOff.name: hwPoePowerOff
hwPoePowerOff.description: This object indicates a PD connected to an interface is powered off.

hwPoePowerOn.name: hwPoePowerOn
hwPoePowerOn.description: This object indicates that a PD connected to an interface is powered on.

hwPoeSlotPowerOverload.name: hwPoeSlotPowerOverload
hwPoeSlotPowerOverload.description: This object indicates that the power consumed by a slot exceeds the threshold.

hwPoeSlotPowerOverloadResume.name: hwPoeSlotPowerOverloadResume
hwPoeSlotPowerOverloadResume.description: This object indicates that the power consumed by a slot does not exceed the threshold.

hwPoePdPowerOverload.name: hwPoePdPowerOverload
hwPoePdPowerOverload.description: This object indicates the power consumed by a PD connected to an interface exceeds the threshold.

hwPoePdPowerOverloadResume.name: hwPoePdPowerOverloadResume
hwPoePdPowerOverloadResume.description: This object indicates that the power consumed by a PD connected to an interface does not exceed the threshold.

hwPoePdConnected.name: hwPoePdConnected
hwPoePdConnected.description: This object indicates that a PD is connected to an interface.

hwPoePdDisconnected.name: hwPoePdDisconnected
hwPoePdDisconnected.description: This object indicates that a PD is disconnected from an interface.

hwPoePdClassInvalid.name: hwPoePdClassInvalid
hwPoePdClassInvalid.description: This object indicates that a PD of an invalid class is detected.

hwPoePdClassOvercurrent.name: hwPoePdClassOvercurrent
hwPoePdClassOvercurrent.description: This object indicates that overcurrent occurs during the classification of a PD.

hwPoePdPowerOvercurrent.name: hwPoePdPowerOvercurrent
hwPoePdPowerOvercurrent.description: This object indicates that overcurrent occurs during the powering of a PD.

hwPoePdPowerOvercurrentResume.name: hwPoePdPowerOvercurrentResume
hwPoePdPowerOvercurrentResume.description: This object indicates that overcurrent is rectified.

hwPoePowerOnFail.name: hwPoePowerOnFail
hwPoePowerOnFail.description: This object indicates that a PD fails to be powered on.

hwPoePowerOffCurrentLimits.name: hwPoePowerOffCurrentLimits
hwPoePowerOffCurrentLimits.description: This object indicates that a PD is powered off because its current meets or exceeds the limit of current.

hwPoePdPriorityDifferent.name: hwPoePdPriorityDifferent
hwPoePdPriorityDifferent.description: This object indicates that the priority of PD is different from the port.

hwPoePowerOverUtilizationThreshold.name: hwPoePowerOverUtilizationThreshold
hwPoePowerOverUtilizationThreshold.description: This object indicates that the PSE is overdrawing power.

hwPoePowerOverUtilizationThresholdResume.name: hwPoePowerOverUtilizationThresholdResume
hwPoePowerOverUtilizationThresholdResume.description: This object indicates that the PSE is not overdrawing power.

hwPoeBoardInsertedWrongFrame.name: hwPoeBoardInsertedWrongFrame
hwPoeBoardInsertedWrongFrame.description: This object indicates that the poe board is inserted in the frame does not support poe.

hwPoePowerAbsent.name: hwPoePowerAbsent
hwPoePowerAbsent.description: This object indicates that the poe power is absent.

hwPoePowerAbsentResume.name: hwPoePowerAbsentResume
hwPoePowerAbsentResume.description: This object indicates that the poe power is present.

hwPoeRpsPowerOutputAlarm.name: hwPoeRpsPowerOutputAlarm
hwPoeRpsPowerOutputAlarm.description: This object indicates that the RPS power can not provide POE power for this device.

hwPoeRpsPowerOutputAlarmResume.name: hwPoeRpsPowerOutputAlarmResume
hwPoeRpsPowerOutputAlarmResume.description: This object indicates that the RPS power can provide POE power for this device.

hwPoeControlChipFail.name: hwPoeControlChipFail
hwPoeControlChipFail.description: This object indicates that the poe control chip is failed.

hwPoeControlChipFailResume.name: hwPoeControlChipFailResume
hwPoeControlChipFailResume.description: This object indicates that the poe control chip has resumed.

hwPoePSEPowerCut.name: hwPoePSEPowerCut
hwPoePSEPowerCut.description: This object indicates that the poe pse power is not enough.

hwPoePSEPowerCutResume.name: hwPoePSEPowerCutResume
hwPoePSEPowerCutResume.description: This object indicates that the poe pse power cut has resumed.

hwPoeSlotPowerCut.name: hwPoeSlotPowerCut
hwPoeSlotPowerCut.description: This object indicates that the poe slot power is not enough.

hwPoeSlotPowerCutResume.name: hwPoeSlotPowerCutResume
hwPoeSlotPowerCutResume.description: This object indicates that the poe slot power cut has resumed.

hwPoeCompliance.name: hwPoeCompliance
hwPoeCompliance.description: The compliance statement for systems supporting this module.

hwPoeSlotGroup.name: hwPoeSlotGroup
hwPoeSlotGroup.description: This object indicates the POE's slot table group.

hwPoePortGroup.name: hwPoePortGroup
hwPoePortGroup.description: This object indicates the POE's port table group.

hwPoeGlobalGroup.name: hwPoeGlobalGroup
hwPoeGlobalGroup.description: This object indicates the POE's global table group.

hwPoeNotificationGroup.name: hwPoeNotificationGroup
hwPoeNotificationGroup.description: This object indicates the POE's notification table group.

hwPoePowerInfoGroup.description: This object indicates the POE's power information table group.
